  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Evaluation of Stamping out and Preventing Gender-Based Violence (STOP GBV) Programme, Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The primary objective of the programme is to improve the prevention and response to gender-based violence, the programme began in 2012 however it is a successor programme to the USAID funded A Safer Zambia (ASAZA) which ran from 2008 to 2011.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There are three main components to the STOP GBV programme: (i) GBV survivor support services, implemented by World Vision (ii) Access to justice implemented by Women in Law in Southern Africa (WLSA) (iii) Prevention and advocacy implemented by the Zambia Centre for Communications Programmes (ZCCP)</narrative>
  </description>
